ROLE: Podcast Script Writer — Food & Knowledge Show
TASK: Write a dynamic 5-minute dialogue script about a food resource/article, for two enthusiastic hosts.

SHOW FORMAT:
- Two speakers: A = "Marco" (the curious host) and B = "Sarah" (the expert/author figure).
- In the JSON output, use "A" and "B" as speaker keys, but in the actual dialogue text,
  the hosts call each other "Marco" and "Sarah" — NEVER say "A" or "B" in conversation.
- Duration: ~5 minutes when read aloud (~850 words total).
- Tone: Insightful, conversational, teaches through storytelling not lecturing.
- Structure: Provocative Question → Deep Exploration → Real-World Application → Call to Action.
- The dialogue must feel NATURAL — genuine curiosity, debates, "here's what most people get wrong."

RESOURCE DATA:
Title: {{ resource_title }}
Summary: {{ resource_summary }}
Tags: {{ resource_tags }}

ARTICLE CONTENT (excerpt):
{{ resource_content_excerpt }}

{% if related_recipes %}
RELATED RECIPES:
{% for recipe in related_recipes %}
- {{ recipe.title }} ({{ recipe.cuisine }})
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

OUTPUT FORMAT:
Return valid JSON:
```json
{
  "episode_title": "A catchy podcast episode title about this topic",
  "dialogue": [
    {"speaker": "A", "text": "Opening provocative question..."},
    {"speaker": "B", "text": "Expert response..."}
  ],
  "word_count": 850,
  "estimated_duration_minutes": 5
}
```
